b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. PhotoRoom is best suited for product photography, background removal, ecommerce listings, social media, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Pixlr AI, meanwhile, shines for photo editing, quick fixes, background removal, browser editing, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2020, PhotoRoom describes itself as \"AI photo editor specialized in product photography and backgrounds.\" Pixlr AI, established in 2008, positions itself as \"Free browser-based AI photo editor with generation features.\" With 12 years between them, Pixlr AI brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while PhotoRoom offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **PhotoRoom** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 5.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Pixlr AI is a poor choice — far from it. Pixlr AI excels in its own right, particularly for photo editing and quick fixes.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best-in-class background removal, go with PhotoRoom. If fully browser-based, no install needed matters more to you, Pixlr AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
